images/

This folder is not for the dataset. It contains images used in your GitHub README to demonstrate the project, such as screenshots, workflow diagrams, and sample results.

images/
├── sample_input.png
├── sample_output.png
└── workflow.png

1. sample_input.png

This should be the original image before processing.

Example:

A conveyor belt with an object.
A bolt or mechanical part before inspection.
The raw camera frame.

2. sample_output.png

This should be the processed output after your program runs.

It should show:

Bounding box around the detected defect.
PASS or FAIL label.
Contours detected.

3. workflow.png

This is a simple block diagram showing how the project works.

Example workflow:

Camera
   │
   ▼
Capture Image
   │
   ▼
Convert to Grayscale
   │
   ▼
Gaussian Blur
   │
   ▼
Thresholding
   │
   ▼
Contour Detection
   │
   ▼
Bounding Box
   │
   ▼
PASS / FAIL

You can create this diagram using:

Microsoft PowerPoint
Canva
draw.io
Microsoft Word (Shapes)
Figma

